  "text": "The optimal diet and the optimal patch utilization vary with prey density and severity of competition (e.g. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Particularly a shift in habitat use may necessitate a shift in food-searching behaviour. Such shifts in foraging behaviour, that are secondary effects of changes in patch utilization, should be clearly distinguished from the changes in food-searching behaviour that are predicted here to follow purely from changes in prey density, and with the predator's utilization pattern of prey and patches unchanged. Where this constraint does not prevail it may be difficult to decide by which mechanism an observed effect is caused.",
